rench names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Wynterheigh was born about 1343, in Dorset, England, United Kingdom, his father, Walter Wynterhay, was 28 and his mother, Alice, was 28. He married ?. He died in 1424, at the age of 82."},"et":{"Abt 1343–1424":"umbes 1343–1424","1343–1424":"1343–1424","1345–1425":"1345–1425","1343–Female":"1343–Surnud","1377–1439":"1377–1439","1379–1429":"1379–1429","1317–1345":"1317–1345","1317–Female":"1317–Surnud","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1379":"1379","1345":"1345","Abt 1343":"umbes 1343","1377":"1377","1343":"1343","ABT 1377":"umbes 1377","about 1379":"umbes 1379","1429":"1429","1439":"1439","1317":"1317",",, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chetnoll,Dorsetshire,England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of,Chetnoll,Dorset,England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1343–1424":"noin 1343–1424","1343–1424":"1343–1424","1345–1425":"1345–1425","1343–Female":"1343–Kuollut","1377–1439":"1377–1439","1379–1429":"1379–1429","1317–1345":"1317–1345","1317–Female":"1317–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1379":"1379","1345":"1345","Abt 1343":"noin 1343","1377":"1377","1343":"1343","ABT 1377":"noin 1377","about 1379":"noin 1379","1429":"1429","1439":"1439","1317":"1317",",, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chetnoll,Dorsetshire,England":"Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of,Chetnoll,Dorset,England":"D